rComments: I took Russian Imperial history and Russian social history with him.  Fantastic lecturer albeit a bit intense (gets up and lectures for an hour straight), but he KNOWS his stuff.  I'd say he was only an easy marker if he knew you and could tell you did the work behind your answers.  I think he's retiring though which is a shame, but he's old so :P
this man knows his stuff. he has all of humanity's history memorized! though one of my lowest marks, i loved the course and the material.

HISB70 -- Prof. Dowler is a very clear and precise lecturer, thus, his lectures were always interesting and enjoyable.  He goes through a lot of material each class at a fairly quick pace, so be prepared to write quickly.  Definitely recommend him.
Really excellent prof, fair marker, and a nice man too.  He teaches at a quick pace, but is very clear about what he's saying.
Quite possibly one of the best profs I have ever had.  He's incredib;y intelligent, approachable and a genuinely nice person.  I highly recommend one of classes to everyone.
Amazing clarity, Brought the whole course together in the final lecture
